  "prompt": "I am 28 years old with 4 years banking experience. What government jobs in India can I apply for?",
  "response": "As a 28-year-old with 4 years of banking experience, you have various government job opportunities in India that you can consider. Here are a few options:\n\n1. **Public Sector Banks**: \n   - Specialist Officer (SO) positions in Public Sector Banks. Your banking experience can be valuable for roles such as Credit Officer, Risk Management Officer, IT Officer, etc.\n   - Probationary Officer (PO) positions through IBPS PO or SBI PO exams.\n\n2. **Reserve Bank of India (RBI)**:\n   - RBI Grade B Officer.\n   - RBI Assistant.\n\n3. **Insurance Sector**:\n   - Administrative Officer (AO) or Assistant positions in insurance companies like LIC, NIC, etc.\n\n4. **Staff Selection Commission (SSC) Exams**:\n   - SSC CGL (Combined Graduate Level) exam for various Group B and C posts in ministries, departments, and organizations of the Government of India.\n\n5. **Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) Exams**:\n   - Civil Services Examination (CSE) for IAS, IPS, IFS, and other central services.\n   - Other specialized exams like Indian Economic Service (IES) and Indian Statistical Service (ISS) if you meet the educational qualifications.\n\n6. **Railway Recruitment Board (RRB) Exams**:\n   - Various Non-Technical Popular Categories (NTPC) positions.\n   - Specialised positions in Railway Finance and Accounts department.\n\n7. **State Public Service Commission Exams**:\n   - State-level Civil Services exams for positions in administrative services, police services, and other departments, specific to your state.\n\n8. **Other Banking-Related Government Posts**:\n   - NABARD (National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development) Grade A and B Officers.\n   - SEBI (Securities and Exchange Board of India) Grade A Officers.\n\n9. **Teaching Positions**:\n   - If interested in academia, consider applying for positions at government universities and colleges as a lecturer or assistant professor (based on your educational qualifications).\n\nTo apply for these positions, you'll need to check the specific eligibility criteria and exam dates from the respective recruitment bodies' official websites.\n",
